Yariv5.name: Yariv5
Yariv5.review_content:
We were looking for a very special place to celebrate our wedding anniversary and we are so happy that we decided to go to HaTraklin. We went to an event called "A meal from the movies" - eleven sumptuous courses accompanied by a delightful host Yossi, short video clips from famous movies, beautiful music and the best waiter - Shay. Everything was perfect - the reception before the meal commenced, the building, the ambiance, the menu, the music - everything. As we didn't really know what to expect, we were overwhelmed by the planning and the consideration taken into presenting and conducting such a wonderful evening even though they've been doing this for ten years!
They really understand the intricacies of preparing meat dishes and the foie gras and carpaccio are the best we have ever tasted. The wine is excellent and we also appreciated that all the dishes were prepared from local Israeli products.
We had the best time and strongly recommend going to "A meal from the movies".
Enjoy!

B0azY.review_content: large quality chunks of meat but for some more delicate ppl in the groups it was less fitting keep it in mind...appetizers are not as exciting and wine selection was good. very nice service a bit overwheling at times
B0azY.name: Boaz Y

MemberProfile-a_uid.B929D7F84A6AA7299B34.name: Laure B
MemberProfile-a_uid.B929D7F84A6AA7299B34.review_content:
As we came for the first time for a dinner date and never heard of them before, we didn't quite know what to expect, but picked it based on the very positive comments I had read here before. A waiter/waitress comes to you in the beginning to explain the history of the building, which gives you the feeling you are having dinner in a very special place, and I believe we were. We ordered the artichoke as an appetizer, which was not that special, albeit good. The moroccan bread is definitely a must as a side, because warm and "better than in Morocco" (so did my beau say, given he's been to Morocco). Their signature dish (seared sirloin) really does the trick as it is quite special to let you cook your meat yourself on the table, and the roka steak was very good too. The meat was not as tender as I expected, but it was still quality meat. As for the wine, we were offered to taste two at the beginning, and we went for a full Malbec which we really appreciated.
Everything went well, to the extent that we were offered a dessert to share (Malabi with vanilla, very good), which was much appreciated as we were celebrating a birthday, until...
Until we got the check, with 80 shekels more than needed, corresponding to nearly 20% of tip, without them giving us any further notice, nor even letting us know that the tip was included. So if we hadn't paid attention, we would have ended up paying not only nearly 20% of tip or "service" (an abnormal sum even for a good restaurant), but tipping on top of it, since in Israel, tips are never included directly in the check, but indeed added later and most often in cash. Although they were quite insistent on having us leaving this tip without further calculation, we could, eventually, pay the initial price and add our own chosen tip (already a good 13%, too bad, we could have left even more...)

Overall great experience but very disappointed due to this. We recommend the place on condition that you check carefully the bill and not let them scam you... I wonder if they do this to only-Israeli groups of people...
MemberProfile-a_uid.B929D7F84A6AA7299B34.review_title: Near to fantastic if not for... an inconvenient tip

160tatianac.review_content: A very nice restaurant locales in Neve Zedek in an old building creating a special atmosphere. Great selection of boutique wines. Chicken liver patte and grilled artichoke are no words amazing. All main meat dishes great as well. Serice is also on a very good level. The only thing to consider - the restaurant is expensive.
cities: Province of Guipuzcoa: San Sebastian - Donostia
Province of A Coruna: Santiago de Compostela
160tatianac.name: Tatiana C

Miss_MayG.name: May G
Miss_MayG.review_content: Traklin came up with a very interesting concept - the present a food scene from a famous movie and then serve the actual dish - that's a really unique experience! The price includes 6 dishes, soft drinks and wine which is very affordable for the quality that they offer. I really like it and will go back next time in TA!

emc545.name: emc545
emc545.review_content: Hatraklin is a delicious restaurant for meat lovers. While there are a vegetarian options, I wouldn't recommend it unless you are a big beef fan. If you are, though, it is a terrific choice. Excellent and attentive service, good Israeli wine choices, and some fantastic desserts. The restaurant is located in a building that is over 100 years old which lends to its charm. All in all a lovely evening for our group of 8 (including 5 teenagers).

naxAdvisor.review_content: The place is beautiful, the service was on point and the food was amazing. We also got wine that was very good. We celebrated our anniversary and will defenently visit again

687jeanines.name: Jeanine S
687jeanines.review_content: We went to Hatraklin on two nights, loved everything there! Our waitress Tamuz was perfect, we got some starters and dessert to taste for free. They also do wine tastings and we had some excellent wines! We ordered vegetarian food as well as their house specialiry, the hot stone. Would come back again, all was perfect!

50raza.name: Raz A
50raza.review_content:
We had awesome night of wine and food. The food was grate and tasty.
3 hours of movies and culinary experience!
I highly recommend it!
50raza.review_title: Amazing night of food and wine

Bouladier_m.name: Bouladier_m
Bouladier_m.review_content:
First night in Tel Aviv and our first dinner was at Hatraklin.
Service was amazing and very well suggested! Typic Israeli food and wine. If you don't know what to eat and which wine to have, trust Ben! With your requests, he knows what's the best for you! Chicken liver pâté is definitely the best in Tel Aviv and what to say of seared sirloin... Delicious and very tasty.
BEST DESSERT EVER! You have to taste Death of chocolate.
Cozy and romantic when you are eating outside!
See you one day Ben! Thanks again

irenashling.name: irenashling
irenashling.review_content:
a special restaurant in the beautiful Neve Zedek located in
a historical building, have great local dishes and local wines

dorona29.name: Doron A
dorona29.review_content:
Movies driven dishes. Each dish is inspired by a movie footage which is screened. Lively hosting in a unique ambience restaurant.
Our team of 30 people spent 3 hours enjoying the movies footage, the music while eating and of course, the food and the wine.

Excellent service contributed to a very good experience.

Nick_NL.review_content:
I made a reservation at this restaurant after reading great comments on TripAdvisor. I always do, and never get get dissapointed before.

So I had great expectations for this place, and I was very happy with what I saw, heard and for all, tasted!

We sat on a table outside. First we had a great conversation with the 'owner' about the (history of the) restaurant and it's food. He told us about the great assortment of wine this place has! (I think about 180 sorts of wine he said). However...nobody of our group drinks wine ore was ready to order. So I have no opinion on that (sorry).

The food we ordered was absolutely fantastic, great portions by the way, and the taste was excellence! I choosed the garlic bread as a starter and as a main course I ordered the porter house T-bone steak of 900 gram wich I - logically - shared with a friend :)

We also got cauliflower in pesto and ailoli as an apetizer (and later a dessert) for free!

The meat was so dilicious and tender, you could wake me up for this (see the picture for an impression). Also the petit fours were amazing. A real chocolate temptation!

The prices are really good value for money and I will go back there when I'm in Tel Aviv again. So if you have a special occasion ore you just want to have a great experience, I can recommend you this place ;)
Nick_NL.name: Nick_NL

PLDI63.review_content:
A no brainer. Very nice place in an old building 100 years old. Was the first hotel in Tel Aviv.
Natali was our server. Very nice. Made us feel welcome and gave us extra treats. Made sure we will be very happy.
They specialize in Israeli grown beef , was very tasteful.

Overall loved the place and will surely come again.
PLDI63.name: PLDI63

GabiKlaf.review_content: Cannot say enough thank you for a magical evening of wine, delicious food, and magical aura. The staff and owner Yosi were soooo amazing, the chopped liver and the artichoke cannot be missed. The meat and the hot stone cook it yourself experience was amazing. I thought things couldn't get better and the the desserts appeared. Cannot wait to go again. My mom is coming to Israel for her 70 th birthday... I know where my two siblings and mom and I will be celebrating. Mwah!
cities: Province of San Jose: San Jose
GabiKlaf.name: GabiKlaf

MemberProfile-a_uid.BFAFC51D58632831921E.review_content:
The meat is excellent.
The chicken curry wasnt good like the rest of the dishes.
The environment is unique for it located in Newe tzedek in a old building once was an hotel. Very retro and beautiful.
MemberProfile-a_uid.BFAFC51D58632831921E.name: Hadas I

Marielle76.name: Marielle76
Marielle76.review_content: What a great service, food, wine, ambiance and people. Just as we had the food in mind before traveling to Israel, delicious! Now we are spoiled...

wshalev.review_content: We had a family dinner at "Meal from the Movies" at this fantastic and unique restaurant. The variety and quality of the eleven (!) courses and accompanying wines added to the unique cinematic experience, the special ambiance of the historic building, and the entertaining talent of the owner made for an enjoyable and memorable experience..
cities: Province of South Tyrol: Nova Levante
wshalev.name: wshalev

rachelio2016.name: Racheli O
rachelio2016.review_content: We had the chance to eat there for two times... The food was very good in both of the times. The place is very nice decorated... The service is a little bit patronising to our opinion... 7 people opinion... Very expensive but the food is really good no doubt about it. I would recommend this restaurant for a romantic date or something special.

yardenelk6.name: yardenelk6
yardenelk6.review_content:
a special restaurant in the beautiful Neve Zedek located in a historical building. and the spacial thing about the restaurant is that all of their products made in Israel!.
they welcomed us with a big smile, and with a lot of good energy. Yonatan, our waiter, was a really big part of our experience, and he knew exactly how to direct us to the right dishes for us, and they were delicious!
if you are looking for an amazing experience, and not only good food- definitely go to the Hatraklin!.

z2017.review_content: We went there with a large group of friends. The waiters and waitresses were great! The steak was cooked perfectly and the chicken was also good. The potatoes and vegetables were some of the best that we had in Israel. The owner came out to greet us. I would definitely consider going there again. Nice, warm atmosphere. Fresh foods. A dinner to remember.
z2017.name: z2017

602daliat.name: Dalia T
602daliat.review_content: The food is ok but nothing to write home about... There is only Israeli wine which sounds very nice till you hear the prices... 220-550 a bottle !!!

Visitor_from_England.name: Visitor_from_England
Visitor_from_England.review_content:
Good, high quality food, no doubt about it. On food alone it would have been 4 star . . . BUT the overall experience was unpleasant, spoiled by “hard sell”:
1. As others have mentioned, they did the ludicrous thing with the wine - asking us to describe what style of wine we liked then bringing two for us to taste and choose from. No pricing information was offered, we had to ask. Their CHEAPEST wines are from NIS265 (c£55) per bottle so be warned. The wine was good, but not worth over £25-£30 in my opinion.
2. We do not like to over-eat so intended to have only mains and desserts, no starters etc. This did not go down well with our waitress who was obviously annoyed and told us that "the mains are going to take a long time, you will need an appetiser or bread". We declined. No more than 5 minutes later our mains appeared so she was obviously just trying it on.
3. Service is automatically added to the bill at just over 11% without this being mentioned on the menu or by the waitress. It is in Hebrew only on the itemised bill, so ask them to explain each item to you if you are not sure about any item. Be careful not to add a gratuity on top if paying by card.
Our bill came to £137 for 2 courses x 2 people, with no coffee or water etc. More than half the cost was wine and service charges.
The food itself was good but the meal was, in my view, comparable to other similar meals we had in Israel, with wine for £80-£90.
Caveat emptor.
Visitor_from_England.review_title: Food good but evening marred by over-priced wine and "hard sell".

Val0205.name: Val0205
Val0205.review_content: Amazing waitress Tamuz great food! Very nice! Food was great hospitality was great and wine is delicious. We recommend!

569israelf.name: Israel F
569israelf.review_content:
There are many great restaurants in Tel Aviv but Hatraklin in Neve Tsedek should be really your first choice! It is not just amazing meat & wine restaurant (delicious appetizers, high quality wine, first quality sirloin with individual roast option and much more) It is also historical building with original floor patterns from over 100 years ago.
We didn't have a chance to join this time but they also run interesting coulinary-movie events 3 times week. You can watch parts of movies with famous dishes while you eat the same dish. Sounds really cool to me. Big thanks to Ben and Jonatan - two great and professional waiters that made our anniversary beautiful and memorable event. The restaurant manager Yossi is a man with a big vision and love to this place and probably that is why this place is so successful and enjoyable to be in. Highly recommended for some family occasions. Shahak and Karolina.
569israelf.review_title: Steak straight from the burning stone!

AJK1941.name: AJK1941
AJK1941.review_content: We split the steak entree; the starters were great and with 2 of them we were satisfied before the steak came. Artichoke Chicken liver pate Dadah cab shraz blend - outstanding!
cities: National Capital Territory of Delhi: New Delhi

moshed62.review_content:
We were there to celebrate my birthday. Fantastic evening... thanks for my wife and despite the restaurant!

The worst par was that we felt every second of our stay that... they are after one thing and one thing only... to make us spend as much as possible... money diary.

It started with a very assertive/aggressive waitresses. Pushing towards the more expansive wines and dishes.

Then the "No wine list" thing... The waitresses brought two wines to taste based on our "liking". She did not even brought two desperate glasses. She poured the 2nd wine to the same glass we drank the first from... We chose the first one, the 2nd was really awful. 265 NIS for a boutique wine we never heard about...

The place is really looking lovely... but we sat next to two very very noisy table... of regulars... so we also got a taste of who really like this restaurant...

As for the food... no, it was NOT bad... but it was lacking any special or unique or wawooo flavor. Also, it was of good, maybe very good ingredients... but nothing that left us with a sensation of wawooo like for example what was so amazing with Mul Yam.

The firsts were good except for the cornflower which was an extra and had no taste.

But the steaks??

Mediocre entrecôte (nothing to write home about) and couple of slices of sirloin to cook by ourselves on a hot stone... that got cold after ten minutes.
And there two (300 NIS together) are this restaurant flagships??

So, what's the point? There are many places that offer just good food + a reasonable wine list (this place does not have a wine list... they have too many wines... never heard such a thing in my life) for much much less money.

The Malabi we took for desert... stay away.... what a ridiculous version taking everything which is good away from it.

But... overall the experience was great thanks to my wife... and despite the restaurant...
moshed62.name: Moshe D

oniaglat.name: oniaglat
oniaglat.review_content:
This a very nice restaurant in a typical house dating from the begining of the 20th century.
Specialy intended for meat lovers and the meat was great.
We were 5 persons and ordered 3 first courses that we shared. the artichok salad was very tasty. Each one of us ordered different meat as main course: entrecote, rum steak ...excellent quality. All the meat are from tge Golan heights
And of course the desserts! A paradise.
Need to mention that the service is excellenr. We had Jonathan who serves us with patience, smile. A real pleasure. He offered us on the house a first coyrse and a dessert!
Excellent evening...
I warmly recommend this place and ask for Jonathan.
